<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<LanguageData>
  
  <!-- EN: Follower -->
  <RI_Sect_Title_A.label>杂役</RI_Sect_Title_A.label>
  <!-- EN: The follower is the lowest rank in a sect, mostly consisting of individuals who are not cultivators but are physically stronger than the average person. They are generally tasked with menial duties such as transporting goods, maintaining sect facilities, and simple errands. -->
  <RI_Sect_Title_A.description>杂役是一个宗门内最底层的存在，大多并不是修炼者，只是体力比一般人略好一些罢了。一般负责一些杂活——运送货物，维护宗门设施，简单的运送任务等。</RI_Sect_Title_A.description>
  
  <!-- EN: Outer disciple -->
  <RI_Sect_Title_B.label>外门弟子</RI_Sect_Title_B.label>
  <!-- EN: Only those with the best talents and wealth can receive the sect's reward of Lingya (spiritual saplings) and become cultivators. Outer sect disciples, in addition to learning and cultivating, also need to complete various tasks assigned by the sect. Those born with special talents, often referred to as "dragons and phoenixes," generally do not stay in the outer sect for long. -->
  <RI_Sect_Title_B.description>只有那些天资最好，家境殷实的年轻人，才能获得来自于宗门的灵芽赏赐，成为一名修炼者。一名外门弟子除了学习与修炼，同时也需要完成宗门布置的诸多任务。至于那些天生灵芽的人中龙凤，则一般不会在外门呆太久。</RI_Sect_Title_B.description>
  
  <!-- EN: Inner disciple -->
  <RI_Sect_Title_C.label>内门弟子</RI_Sect_Title_C.label>
  <!-- EN: Once a cultivator's level reaches a certain stage, they can enter the inner sect. Here, they will no longer be subjected to the rough collective education but will instead receive a personalized educational plan, with supervision from the elders of the sect. -->
  <RI_Sect_Title_C.description>当修炼境界提升至一定的境界，便可以踏入内门。在这里将会脱离粗糙的集体教育，转而为每个内门弟子设计个性化的教育方案，并且由宗门内的长老负责监督。</RI_Sect_Title_C.description>
  
  <!-- EN: Direct disciple -->
  <RI_Sect_Title_D.label>亲传弟子</RI_Sect_Title_D.label>
  <!-- EN: Among the inner sect disciples, those with exceptional talents who stand out will be promoted to direct disciples under the elders' tutelage. These fortunate individuals will accompany the elders and receive direct teachings from them. -->
  <RI_Sect_Title_D.description>那些具有特殊天赋，在内门弟子中崭露头角的年轻人，将会在长老的提携下转为亲传弟子。这些幸运儿将会跟随于长老左右，直接受到来自于长老的教导。</RI_Sect_Title_D.description>
  
  <!-- EN: Elder -->
  <RI_Sect_Title_E.label>长老</RI_Sect_Title_E.label>
  <!-- EN: Becoming an elder is a difficult condition, requiring a disciple to undergo years of hard work and make significant contributions to the sect to secure a place in the election. Elders hold immense power, directly answering to the sect leader and receiving generous salaries from the sect's total revenue. -->
  <RI_Sect_Title_E.description>成为长老的条件可谓苛刻，需要一名宗门弟子经历长期的打拼奋斗，为宗门做出巨大贡献，才能在竞选队伍中占有一席之地。而长老的权利可谓是巨大的，他们直接受到掌门的调遣，并且可以从宗门总收入中获得高昂的薪水。</RI_Sect_Title_E.description>
  
  <!-- EN: Master -->
  <RI_Sect_Title_F.label>掌门</RI_Sect_Title_F.label>
  <!-- EN: The sect leader is the highest-ranking individual in the sect and is often the most powerful fighter. The leader is usually elected from among the elders, although there are other ways to become the sect leader. They are responsible for many administrative affairs and must also strengthen their own cultivation, so the sect leader often remains in seclusion, becoming what disciples refer to as an "old monster." -->
  <RI_Sect_Title_F.description>掌门是一个宗门的最高负责人，同时往往也是战力最高的人。掌门通常从长老之中选举而出，也有许多其他成为掌门的方式。他们需要负责诸多管理事务，同时也要巩固自身的境界，所以一个宗门的掌门往往闭关不出，成为弟子口中的“老怪物”。</RI_Sect_Title_F.description>
  
</LanguageData>